text: I need to write a function that returns true if the dictionary has duplicates in it.
So pretty much if anything appears in the dictionary more than once, it will return true.
Here is what I have but I am very far off and not sure what to do.

code:
d = {"a", "b", "c"}

def has_duplicates(d):
    seen = set()
    d={}
    for x in d:
        if x in seen:
            return True
        seen.add(x)
    return False

print has_duplicates(d)
